Anonymous Sun 08 Mar 2020 21:30:50 No.28835351 Report
Quoted By: >>28835629 >>28841067
>>28834195
>>28832393

I don't give a shit what people say, we need more greens like this. We longer, more lewd, more snuggles/cuddles and more wholesome. Childhood friends growing up with each other. Learning what sex is with each other. Being each others best friend and having a family together. It's a simple premise and one that alot of new writers can do with a lot of reference. Also I think stories of this nature are good for trying out new species. You will get less hanged up on the story (b/c you more or less know how it goes, but you give it your own take, which can make everyone unique) and focus more on species traits, family/societal dynamics, and how the cycles of growing up are unique to each species. More indepth species stories leads to more species stories in general. For example:

Lizards/snakes
>eggs, friend's mom keeps her egg like a picture
>need for heat, friend has cool heating room thing

Frogs/salamanders
>slime, friend has weird grooming rituals do deal with it
>the whole tadpole to frog thing; first years as friends where between glass

Marsupials
>friend keeps games inside pouch, your the only one who has seen the inside of it.
>she uses it to sneak in snacks for the both of you

Bats
>friend uses echolocation to find bugs so yall can fish.
>uses wings like a tent when you were little and you made finger puppets on them
